# AWS Password policy

The AWS Password policy is like any other secure password policy which consists of the following points:
    - Specifying minimum password length (x characters)
    - Requires inclusion of Uppercase letters
    - Lowercase letters
    - Numbers
    - Non-alphanumeric character
    - Allow all IAM Users to change their own passwords login
    - Requires users to change their password after some time (password expiration)
    - Password reuse prevention
    - Multifactor authentication (MFA)
        i. Physical device
        ii. Google Authenticator
        iii. Authy (support for multiple token on phone)
        iv. Universal 2nd Factor Security Key (U2F)

 
